News for medicalterms-20050703
==============================

This release fixes two errors in the Makefile, which made the
creation of distribution packages really annoying.

Furthermore, there's a new category of words. I've included the
generic names for most usual drugs.

In the already distributed word lists were some typo fixes applied
and quite a few more words added.

And last, but not least, the creation of this NEWS file makes
the package suitable for "gnu" rules in the configure.ac file
instead of "foreign". In addition, the NEWS file is checked for
the current release number before actually shipping the tarball.

 -- Tobias Toedter <t.toedter@gmx.net>  Sun, 03 Jul 2005 19:11:17 +0200
